## DermaMind – Skin Analysis Prototype
A university project demonstrating an end‑to‑end mobile and backend skin analysis system.

## Overview
DermaMind is a mobile prototype that allows users to capture or upload a skin photo, sends it to a Node.js backend for heuristic image analysis using Sharp, and returns an AI‑style assessment including:
- Predicted skin condition
- Confidence score
- Severity level
- Skin metrics (redness, texture, inflammation, brightness)
- Basic skincare recommendations
This is a university prototype, not a medical tool.

## Core Features Implemented
- Take a photo using device camera
- Upload from gallery
- Animated upload + progress bar
- AI‑style results screen
- Condition prediction
- Confidence
- Severity
- Animated metric bars
- Recommendations
- Metadata
- Scan history stored locally (AsyncStorage)
- User authentication (signup/login)
- Protected profile screen
- Terms of Use & Privacy Notice
- Clean, consistent UI with animations
# Backend (Node.js + Express + MongoDB)
- JWT authentication
- Password hashing (bcrypt)
- Image upload via Multer (memory storage)
- Image analysis using Sharp statistics
- Heuristic classification logic
- Confidence + severity scoring
- MongoDB user storage
- Clean, modular routes

## System Architecture
React Native App
   ├── Camera / Gallery
   ├── Upload image → /api/analysis/upload
   ├── Display results
   └── Save history locally
Node.js Backend
   ├── /api/auth (register/login)
   ├── /api/user/profile (protected)
   └── /api/analysis/upload (image analysis)
MongoDB
   └── Stores user accounts

