# How to Run the Project
## Backend Setup (Node.js + MongoDB)
1. Clone the repo
   git clone <your-repo-url>
cd backend

2. Install dependencies
   npm install

3. Create .env file
  MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/dermamind
  JWT_SECRET=your_secret_here
  PORT=5001

4. Start MongoDB
Local mongod
OR MongoDB Atlas connection string

5. Run the backend (Ensure you are specifically in the src folder as that is where the server.js is located)
   node server.js

6. Test the server
   http://localhost:5001/
   You should see: { "message": "DermaMind API running" }

## Mobile App Setup (React Native)
Note: Running the mobile app requires a full React Native environment (Android Studio or Xcode).
If unavailable, please refer to the demo video.

1. Install dependencies
   cd app
   npm install

2. Update backend IP address
   In ScanScreen.tsx and UploadPhoto.tsx: "http://<your-local-ip>:5001/api/analysis/upload"

3. Run the app
   Android: npx react-native run-android
   
   iOS: npx pod-install ios
   npx react-native run-ios

